    <td rowspan="2" valign="top"><a onMouseUp="MM_openBrWindow('/issue9/artwork.html','','width=600,height=500')" href="#"><img height="242" alt="Click to enlarge picture." src="/issue9/art_small.jpg" width="292" border="0" name="home_r2_c2"></a></td>
    <td rowspan="2"><img height="10" alt="" src="/images/spacer.gif" width="17" border="0" name="home_r2_c3"></td>
    <td colspan="2" valign="top" class="titulo2">Dear Guest,</td>
    <td><img height="23" alt="" src="/images/issue_img/spacer.gif" width="1" border="0"></td>
  </tr>
  <tr> 
    <td colspan="2" valign="top" class="texto2"><p><br>  
      I am delighted to welcome 
      you to Issue 9 of <i>The International Literary Quarterly</i>. </p>
      <p>First of all, the review’s Board of Editors would like to take this opportunity to introduce the following distinguished figures from the worlds of literature and the arts, all of whom have kindly agreed to act as Consulting Editors of Interlitq with effect from this issue: <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/frank-ankersmit/bio.php">Frank Ankersmit</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/reza-aslan/bio.php">Reza Aslan</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/michael-barry/bio.php">Michael Barry</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/jean-boase-beier/bio.php">Jean Boase-Beier</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/mario-biagioli/bio.php">Mario Biagioli</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/stanley-cavell/bio.php">Stanley Cavell</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/hollis-clayson/bio.php">Hollis Clayson</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/sarah-churchwell/bio.php">Sarah Churchwell</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/kristina-cordero/bio.php">Kristina Cordero</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/drucilla-cornell/bio.php">Drucilla Cornell</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/andre-dombrowski/bio.php">André Dombrowski</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/klaus-ebner/bio.php">Klaus Ebner</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/orlando-figes/bio.php">Orlando Figes</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/nancy-fraser/bio.php">Nancy Fraser</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/maureen-freely/bio.php">Maureen Freely</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/michael-fried/bio.php">Michael Fried</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/lydia-goehr/bio.php">Lydia Goehr</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/lawrence-grossberg/bio.php">Lawrence Grossberg</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/elizabeth-grosz/bio.php">Elizabeth Grosz</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/valerie-henitiuk/bio.php">Valerie Henitiuk</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/martin-kern/bio.php">Martin Kern</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/joseph-koerner/bio.php">Joseph Koerner</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/mabel-lee/bio.php">Mabel Lee</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/linda-leith/bio.php">Linda Leith</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue8/edie_meidav/bio.php">Edie Meidav</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/jack-miles/bio.php">Jack Miles</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/laura-mulvey/bio.php">Laura Mulvey</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/azar-nafisi/bio.php">Azar Nafisi</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/sari-nusseibeh/bio.php">Sari Nusseibeh</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/clare-pettitt/bio.php">Clare Pettitt</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue7/robert_pinsky/bio.php">Robert Pinsky</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/francois-rigolot/bio.php">Fran&ccedil;ois Rigolot</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/carla-sassi/bio.php">Carla Sassi</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/mongolian/bio.php">Hadaa Sendoo</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/miranda-seymour/bio.php">Miranda Seymour</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/mimi-sheller/bio.php">Mimi Sheller</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/elaine-showalter/bio.php">Elaine Showalter</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/penelope-shuttle/bio.php">Penelope Shuttle</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/julian-stallabrass/bio.php">Julian Stallabrass</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/marjorie-trusted/bio.php">Marjorie Trusted</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/vianu/bio.php">Lidia Vianu</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/victor-vitanza/bio.php">Victor Vitanza</a> and <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/staff/david-wellbery/bio.php">David Wellbery</a>.</p></td>
    <td><img height="219" alt="" src="/images/issue_img/spacer.gif" width="1" border="0"></td>
  </tr>
  <tr> 
    <td colspan="4" rowspan="2" valign="top" class="texto2">
   &nbsp;<br>
        <p><span lang="EN-US">In terms of contributions to Issue 9, I hope that you&nbsp;will enjoy the evocative poetry of <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/bernstein/job.php">Ilya Bernstein</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/delaplaine/job.php">Joanne Rocky Delaplaine</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/hartman/job.php">Geoffrey Hartman</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/haynes/job.php">John Haynes</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/kinloch/job.php">David Kinloch</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/padel/job.php">Ruth Padel</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/serio/job.php">Chris Serio</a> and <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/trinidad/job.php">David Trinidad</a>; the arresting prose of <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/robertson/job.php#french">Fran&ccedil;oise Brodsky</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/jorge_edwards/job.php">Jorge Edwards</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/robertson/job.php#bulgarian">Tsvetanka Elenkova</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/robertson/job.php#german">Rebecca Jany</a> and <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/robertson/job.php">Peter Robertson</a>; the trenchant criticism of <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/filippakopoulou/job.php">Maria Filippakopoulou</a>; and <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/vianu/job.php">Lidia Vianu&rsquo;s</a> informative interview with Stephen Wilson.</span></p>
        <p><span lang="EN-US">Readers will also note the inclusion in this issue of &ldquo;Volta: A Multilingual Anthology&rdquo;, constituting &ldquo; a celebration of multilinguism and diversity&rdquo;, showcasing the poem&nbsp;<em>Volta</em>&nbsp;by Richard Berengarten, dedicated to the memory of the&nbsp;Greek poet,&nbsp;George Seferis, and translated into seventy-four different languages by the following authors:&nbsp;</span><span lang="EN-US"><a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/urdu/bio.php">Nausheen Ahmad</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/punjabi/bio.php">Toheed Ahmad</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/latvian/bio.php">Amanda Aizpuriete</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/nupe/bio.php">Baba Akote</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/danish/bio.php">Agnar Art&uacute;vertin</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/azerbaijan/bio.php">Mammed Aslan</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/malay/bio.php">Razif Bahari</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/hausa/bio.php">Ismail Bala</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/yiddish/bio.php">Mary Blum Devor</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/german/bio.php">Theo Breuer</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/northeastenglish/bio.php">Kevin Cadwallander</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/portuguese/bio.php">Helena Cardoso</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/kurdish/bio.php">Firat Cewer&icirc;</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/arumonian/bio.php">Lila Cona</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/french/bio.php">Robert Davreu</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/shetlandic/bio.php">Christine De Luca</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/runyakole/bio.php">Tumusiime Katwende Deo</a></span><span lang="EN-US">,&nbsp;<a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/spanish/bio.php">Paul Scott Derrick</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/macedonian/bio.php">Vasil Filipov</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/bengali/bio.php">Bashabi Fraser</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/southalemmanicdornbernisch/bio.php">Ulrich Gabriel</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/georgian/bio.php">Manana Gelashvili</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/hungarian/bio.php">George G&ouml;m&ouml;ri</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/maltese/bio.php">Maria Grech Ganado</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/arabic/bio.php">Hassan Hilmi</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/breton/bio.php">Rhisiart Hincks</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/sindhi/bio.php">Fahmida Hussain</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/basque/bio.php">Juan Kruz Igerabide Sarasola</a>,&nbsp;<a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/finnish/bio.php">Jouni Inkala</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/ibibio/bio.php">Ofonime Inyang</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/slovenian/bio.php">Ana Jelnikar</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/czech/bio.php">Miroslav Jindra</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/japanese/bio.php">Tomoko Kanda</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/estonian/bio.php">Maarja Kangro</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/slovak/bio.php">Jana Kantorov&aacute;-B&aacute;likov&aacute;</a>,  <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/greek/bio.php">Ilias Layios</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/dutch/bio.php">Jan Lauwereyns</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/galician/bio.php">Fernando Lavandeira</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/persian/bio.php">Parvin Loloi</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/uzbek/bio.php">Akhmad hoji Khorazmiy</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/croatian/bio.php">Tomislav Kuzmanovi&#263;</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/scottishgaelic/bio.php">Aonghas MacNeacail</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/ukrainian/bio.php">Vasyl Makhno</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/russian/bio.php">Olga Markelova</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/sepedi/bio.php">Mawatle J. Mojalefa</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/italian/bio.php">Paola Musa</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/lumasaba/bio.php">Bob Natifu</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/turkish/bio.php">Annakuly Nurmammedov</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/ebira/bio.php">Sunday Enessi Ododo</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/igbo/bio.php">Obododimma Oha</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/nigerianpidgin/bio.php">Wilson Orhiunu</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/nepali/bio.php">Hom Paribag</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/triestino/bio.php">Toni Piccini</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/afrikaans/bio.php">Henning Pieterse</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/lithuanian/bio.php">Sara Poisson</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/catalan/bio.php">Begonya Pozo</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue7/vera_radojevic/bio.php">Vera V. Radojevi&#263;</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/galician/bio.php">Loreto Riveiro &Aacute;lvarez</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/scots/bio.php">James Robertson</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/irishgaelic/bio.php">Gabriel Rosenstock</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/welsh/bio.php">Eurig Salisbury</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/norwegian/bio.php">Jostein S&aelig;b&oslash;e</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/mongolian/bio.php">Hadaa Sendoo</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/albanian/bio.php">Resul Shabani</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/swedish/svenbrobio.php">Jesper Svenbro</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/swedish/bio.php">Lars-H&aring;kan Svensson</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/chinese/bio.php">Chee-Lay Tan</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/bulgarian/bio.php">Petar Tchouhov</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/spanish/teruelbio.php">Miguel Teruel</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/yoruba/bio.php">Kola Tubosun</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/romanian/bio.php">R&#259;zvan Voncu</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/polish/bio.php">El&#380;bieta W&oacute;jcik-Leese</a>, <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/kyrgyz/bio.php">Soltobay Zaripbekov</a> and <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/volta/hebrew/bio.php">Ariel Zinder</a>.</span> </p>
      <p><span lang="EN-US">And, last but not least, all of these texts are thrown into splendid relief by the highly atmospheric artwork of <a class="link1" href="http://interlitq.org/issue9/macalpine/bio.php">Jean Macalpine</a>, Guest Artist for this issue of <em>Interlitq</em>.</span></p>
        <p><span lang="EN-US">I very much hope that you will enjoy Issue 9 of&nbsp;<em>The International Literary Quarterly</em>, and that you will return to visit us in February 2010.</span></p>


<br>
		<br>
        With warm regards,<br>
        <a href="http://www.interlitq.org/staff/peter_robertson/bio.php" class="link1">Peter 
        Robertson </a>
